The paper deals with achieving high rate, low delay communication over edge paths where the bottleneck is an 802.11ac WLAN. This involves issues related to network infrastructure, communication protocols, and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with information theory and communication theory, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as the second likely category. The paper also involves multimedia communication, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as the third likely category. The paper also deals with security and privacy issues, which suggests cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the fourth likely category. Finally, the paper involves machine learning techniques, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the fifth likely category.
